{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"acd5524f-ea47-4ca5-aaea-d3d623621b58","content":"I'd be happy to help analyze your .dmp crash dump file! I don't see the file in the current directory though.\n\nHere's what I can help with:\n\n1. **Using `dotnet-dump analyze`** — the primary tool for .NET crash dumps\n2. **Using `lldb` with SOS** — for lower-level analysis\n\nTo get started, I need:\n\n1. **Where is your .dmp file?** (provide the path or upload it)\n2. **What .NET version** is the app targeting? (e.g., .NET 6, 8, 9)\n3. **What symptoms did you observe?** (unhandled exception, segfault, hang, OOM, etc.)\n\nOnce I have the dump file path, I can install `dotnet-dump` and run commands like:\n- `clrstack` — managed call stacks\n- `pe` (print exception) — last thrown exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` — heap analysis for OOM\n- `threads` — all thread states\n\nLet me know the file location and I'll dig in!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0f7c0544-a4db-4883-bf2e-046a68c2eae3","outputTokens":253,"requestId":"C3CD:A78B9:1DDDE3B:2184004:6A07C3F6"},"id":"a22310ba-677e-46a3-9b4e-973c88027af5","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:10:22.789Z","parentId":"923b4043-2bc5-423c-bf8e-940f9aed166c"}
